Durban - Bone fragments believed to be the remains of kidnapped businessman Sikhumbuzo Mjwara, the owner of uMhlanga’s upmarket Barrio Restaurant, are going to be sent for DNA testing. 
This was revealed during the bail application of Pietermaritzburg security guard Nkosiphile Ndlovu who is believed to be the hitmen. 

Ndlovu, who abandoned his bail application in the Verulam Magistrate's Court on Monday, apparently did a pointing out to police of where Mjwara's remains were. 
The remains were found in a cemetery in Pietermaritzburg and will be sent to Pretoria for DNA testing this week the court heard. AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
Ndlovu was among four people allegedly linked to the kidnapping. 
Related ArticlesPietermaritzburg policemen linked to Durban businessman's kidnappingAnother cop arrested for kidnapped Barrio restaurant owner
The businessman was kidnapped on August 30 outside the Verulam Magistrate'sCourt. 
Three policemen- Sergeant Thabane Cyril Ndlovu, Constable Collen Makhaye and Jerome Dumisani Ngubane- were released on R3000 bail on Monday. 
They were arrested by Warrant officer Bob Pillay of the provincial police task team. 

The matter was adjourned for November 23. 
The motive of the kidnapping is unknown. 
